<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-26-0464 </DOCNO><TEXT>On April 6, 1987, the cellars of the Institute of Molecular Biology andBiochemistry at the Free University of Berlin were flooded. Two of therooms affected were decay stores for radioactively contaminated laboratorymaterials. There was a risk of contamination of the flood water with3-H, C-14, P-32, S-35 and I-125. The method of cleaning up used by thefire brigade is portrayed, taking account of decontamination measures.</TEXT></DOC>